Admin Checklist for Workforce Engagement

Workforce Engagement is available in Lightning Experience, Available in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

Step 1. Set up Workforce Engagement.

Step 2. Add the Time Slots related list to the Operating Hours object and create operating hours with time slots to represent your centers' operating hours.

Step 3. Create service territories, which will be used by Workforce Engagement to set the time zone in data views.

Step 4. If using queue-based routing, enable Omni-Channel, set up queues, and associate routing configurations to your queues.

Step 5. Create workload histories and intelligent forecasts for queues-based routing.

Step 6. If not using a queue-based routing workflow, create or select a channel object and choose filters for workload history and forecast's dashboard data graph view.

Step 7. Map fields to Skills filter, Region filter, and Custom filter.

Step 8. Import channel data from Salesforce using Data Loader or another integration tool if it is not already in Salesforce.

Create Omni-Channel Queues for Workforce Engagement and route assignments to agent teams.
title: Setting Up Workforce Engagement for Workload History and Forecast
